Enoorez its the everse of Zeroone so it could be binary, lets check in python by replacing text by 0 or 1:

```
>s = ""
>s = s.replace("eno","1")
>s = s.replace("orez","0"
```

We notice that there is text with some hex , so i tried to keep just alpha chars : 

```
>b = ''.join([ i if i.isalpha() else '' for i in decode_binary_string(s)])

result >''


```


Seem like we will loop again with "oez" = "0" and "oe" = "1" :

```
> b = b.replace("oez","0")
> b = b.replace("eo","1")
> ''.join([ i if i.isalpha() else '' for i in decode_binary_string(b)])
result > 'TUCTFMnYLYeRMThNk'

```
